  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Social Work Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Beneficiaries' assistance and Family Development Programmes</strong></p><ul><li><p>Conduct needs assessments through focus group discussions, interviews, and home visits to better understand family dynamics, challenges, and strengths.</p></li><li><p>Provide casework support and appropriate referrals for issues such as financial difficulties and access to community resources.</p></li><li><p>Maintain up-to-date case records and beneficiary databases</p></li><li><p>Work collaboratively with volunteers, partner agencies and internal teams to coordinate support plans</p></li><li><p>Develop and facilitate family-focused programmes, workshops, and engagement activities tailored to beneficiaries' needs.</p></li><li><p>Prepare communication materials to inform families about services and events, and respond to queries through various channels.</p></li><li><p>Administer interim support and check-ins for vulnerable families</p></li><li><p>Support event planning and logistics for family engagement activities, ensuring positive and meaningful interactions for participants.</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Assistance Disbursement Event</strong></p><ul><li><p>Support the overall coordination of the assistance disbursement event, ensuring activities were aligned with the intended goals.</p></li><li><p>Assist with cross-team collaboration across logistics, volunteer engagement, and administration to maintain smooth operations.</p></li><li><p>Facilitate communication with external stakeholders and sponsors.</p></li><li><p>Manage day-to-day interactions with beneficiaries, including intake processes, needs assessments, and follow-ups.</p></li><li><p>Plan and carry out distribution of rations and vouchers, as well as family engagement activities.</p></li><li><p>Budget tracking and administrative tasks.<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in Social Work (or related discipline).</p></li><li><p>At least 2 years of relevant experience in social service, casework support and community programmes</p></li><li><p>Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and relevant experience.</p></li></ul>",
